1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 6=

3
00:01:44,660 --> 00:01:45,140
Thank you.

4
00:01:47,220 --> 00:01:47,740
Ms. Lin.

5
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:51,088
(Signed Author Copyright Agreement)
I wrote a draft for "Drunk Old Friend".

6
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,500
Could you please tell me

7
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:56,100
exactly how my writing
was worse than Gu Yan's?

8
00:01:56,288 --> 00:01:57,888
You didn't write worse than him.

9
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,660
You actually wrote
a better opening than he did.

10
00:02:02,540 --> 00:02:04,020
It's just that he wrote faster.

11
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:07,300
But I was brought
into the project later than he was.

12
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:08,420
I didn't expect

13
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:10,340
this project to be
pushed forward so suddenly.

14
00:02:10,866 --> 00:02:12,740
I thought there'd be
three or four months left.

15
00:02:13,020 --> 00:02:14,260
If that had been the case,

16
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:15,844
maybe I would've

17
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,060
chosen you,

18
00:02:17,660 --> 00:02:19,700
and had Gu Yan
drop this project for something else.

19
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:22,500
So this isn't fair at all.

20
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:30,660
In a sense,

21
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:32,340
it is fair.

22
00:02:34,940 --> 00:02:35,820
In the face of fate.

23
00:02:41,380 --> 00:02:42,820
No one must know

24
00:02:42,820 --> 00:02:43,650
you did a test draft

25
00:02:43,660 --> 00:02:44,740
for Drunk Old Friend.

26
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,300
That's the first agreement.

27
00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:49,340
As for the second one,

28
00:02:49,620 --> 00:02:50,580
after you sign it,

29
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:52,888
I'll show you
the proposal for the second story.

30
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:56,220
Will it be two people
competing again this time?

31
00:02:57,180 --> 00:02:58,260
There are five.

32
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:59,900
There are four others.

33
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:02,580
But they already
started writing a few days ago.

34
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:04,610
Ms. Lin,

35
00:03:04,610 --> 00:03:06,711
other companies
don't do pitch competitions like this.

36
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:08,355
You can write better than they can.

37
00:03:12,580 --> 00:03:13,220
Show him.

38
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:15,733
This is the proposal.

39
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:17,780
Can I read it now?

40
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:19,860
Don't I need to sign
a non-disclosure agreement?

41
00:03:19,980 --> 00:03:22,044
Read it.
You won't be able to turn it down.

42
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:23,780
Stay with him.

43
00:03:23,860 --> 00:03:24,990
I need to go pick someone up.

44
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,088
Thank you, Ms. Lin.

45
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:37,740
Guys!

46
00:03:38,340 --> 00:03:39,020
Did you hear?

47
00:03:39,066 --> 00:03:40,500
Gu Yan is coming to the office soon.

48
00:03:40,980 --> 00:03:41,980
I heard about it.

49
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,700
The 10 AM meeting is to introduce him.

50
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:46,020
When did

51
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:47,260
Ms. Lin start

52
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:48,300
training Gu Yan?

53
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:49,911
It's been at least a year.

54
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:51,340
I'm guessing

55
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:52,940
that if Ling Yikai

56
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:55,140
and Zhao Lanxin
hadn't suddenly jumped ship,

57
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:57,980
she would've kept him hidden longer.

58
00:03:58,180 --> 00:03:59,380
I heard

59
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:01,460
she signed several authors externally.

60
00:04:01,460 --> 00:04:03,380
Only Gu Yan survived in the end.

61
00:04:03,860 --> 00:04:06,940
The success of one general
is built on the bones of ten thousand.

62
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:08,060
So,

63
00:04:08,133 --> 00:04:09,180
she probably has backups

64
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:10,460
for people like us, too.

65
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:11,420
She can replace us.

66
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,500
I thought our boss was sweet and naive.

67
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,420
But she's just as calculating.

68
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:19,540
Tense, anxious, and paranoid.

69
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:25,300
This book, "Oblivious and Unhappy",

70
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,060
is pretty good.

71
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:27,300
I'll read it.

72
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:28,620
Ms. Lin.

73
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:32,380
Why are you covered in sweat?

74
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:34,700
I took the bus here. I ran a bit,

75
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:35,700
so I wouldn't be late.

76
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:36,822
I'll walk you to the junction.

77
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:37,300
Let's go.

78
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:42,980
Is that Gu Yan?

79
00:04:44,180 --> 00:04:44,900
I think so.

80
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:48,100
Do you know

81
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,380
why that guy kept staring at you?

82
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:50,740
Why?

83
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:52,660
He also

84
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:53,500
wrote a draft.

85
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:54,820
You came out on top.

86
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:56,180
So he put his pen down.

87
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,340
Thank you,

88
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:00,820
for this opportunity.

89
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:02,620
You earned it yourself.

90
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,066
I didn't give it to you.

91
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:04,866
Right here.

92
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:09,577
Morning, Ms. Lin.

93
00:05:09,622 --> 00:05:11,100
Cindy, this is Gu Yan.

94
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:12,120
Please take care of him.

95
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,260
Show him around the office.

96
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:14,540
Introduce him to everyone.

97
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:15,740
Will do, Ms. Lin.

98
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:17,220
Mr. Gu Yan.

99
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:19,660
Please sign in.

100
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:35,780
Ms. Lin.

101
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:37,977
It's all signed?

102
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:39,700
He barely read it before signing.

103
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,180
He said he wouldn't

104
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:42,822
let the opportunity slip away this time.

105
00:05:44,644 --> 00:05:45,860
As long as he has that drive.

106
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:47,420
Ms. Lin.

107
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:49,260
I have a question...

108
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:51,380
for you.

109
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:55,020
Are you going to ask

110
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:56,060
how many are now

111
00:05:56,266 --> 00:05:57,900
working back-to-back
on each project?

112
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:00,911
Different projects
are handled differently.

113
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,980
For proposals that are good

114
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:04,340
and show promise,

115
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:05,540
I'll assign

116
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,688
several groups
to write them separately.

117
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,980
Isn't that really...

118
00:06:10,755 --> 00:06:13,244
Wouldn't the people
who aren't chosen feel cheated?

119
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:15,700
I just saw Sanzang
and felt pretty bad for him.

120
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,688
Losing out on skill isn't being cheated.

121
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,660
Then, what about Gu Yan's situation?

122
00:06:19,688 --> 00:06:20,700
Now that it's decided

123
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:21,820
that he'll continue writing

124
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,620
"Drunk Old Friend",

125
00:06:22,688 --> 00:06:24,800
he'll be the only one
writing it from now on, right?

126
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,300
There won't be any other backups?

127
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:29,180
Of course not.

128
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:34,220
That's a relief.

129
00:06:34,340 --> 00:06:35,666
I'd like to introduce everyone

130
00:06:35,822 --> 00:06:36,380
to Gu Yan.

131
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:44,780
Over the past year or so,

132
00:06:45,060 --> 00:06:47,244
Gu Yan and I
were still getting to know each other.

133
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:48,300
So, we agreed

134
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,580
to keep things quiet.

135
00:06:49,977 --> 00:06:52,020
We waited until
the first fifty chapters were out

136
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:53,955
before making
further plans for our collab.

137
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:56,020
I can now tell you all

138
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:57,940
that we have actually finished

139
00:06:57,940 --> 00:06:59,180
the first 120 chapters.

140
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:02,540
And film adaptation rights
are already being negotiated.

141
00:07:05,580 --> 00:07:05,980
Go on.

142
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:11,060
Although it's my name

143
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,940
on the author line,

144
00:07:13,620 --> 00:07:14,420
the truth is that

145
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:15,700
most of the credit

146
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:17,380
goes to Ms. Lin.

147
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:20,140
I don't have much going on usually.

148
00:07:20,711 --> 00:07:21,580
Except for sleeping,

149
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:25,180
I spend all my time
writing novels with her.

150
00:07:26,288 --> 00:07:28,260
We have a lot of authors
with good attitudes.

151
00:07:28,466 --> 00:07:29,340
Lawyer Bei is here.

152
00:07:29,860 --> 00:07:32,620
But a top-tier author
with an attitude this good?

153
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:34,380
You're the first.

154
00:07:34,540 --> 00:07:35,860
- Impressive!
- Absolutely!

155
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:36,820
Let's give him a hand!

156
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:38,020
Come on!

157
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:49,700
Mr. Bei.

158
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:52,000
This is thick.

159
00:07:52,460 --> 00:07:53,420
Per your request,

160
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,820
I've detailed clauses covering

161
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:55,955
the partnership duration,

162
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:56,820
content scope,

163
00:07:57,180 --> 00:07:58,260
copyright confidentiality,

164
00:07:58,260 --> 00:07:59,400
and decision-making power.

165
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:00,620
Once he gets here,

166
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,060
I'll walk him through it.

167
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:03,420
You need not be present.

168
00:08:03,740 --> 00:08:04,940
I can handle the negotiations.

169
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:07,380
Okay, thanks.

170
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:10,820
Gu Yan.

171
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,780
Wait in Ms. Lin's office for a bit.

172
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,940
She's having a quick word with Mr. Bei.

173
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,180
She'll call you in later.

174
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:20,180
Water.

175
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:28,300
Since we have a minute,

176
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,140
I want to confirm a few things with you.

177
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:31,700
Your home address

178
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,180
and your daily schedule.

179
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:37,540
We'll add each other on WeChat.

180
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,977
If I need to chase you for drafts

181
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:39,740
or if the company...

182
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:40,180
No need.

183
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:43,620
What do you mean?

184
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:46,666
I'll just contact Ms. Lin directly.

185
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:50,700
Let me reintroduce myself.

186
00:08:50,820 --> 00:08:52,580
Cai Zhangzhu, Lin Zhanqiao's assistant.

187
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,180
Part of my job

188
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:56,060
is maintaining
her relationships with authors.

189
00:08:56,540 --> 00:08:57,140
She's busy.

190
00:08:57,660 --> 00:08:59,460
I handle
all the trivial stuff for her first.

191
00:08:59,660 --> 00:09:01,820
Ms. Lin handles my affairs directly.

192
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,660
Why are you so two-faced?

193
00:09:06,755 --> 00:09:08,300
You're all nice in front of Ms. Lin.

194
00:09:08,540 --> 00:09:10,266
When she's gone, you're just arrogant.

195
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:15,700
I only talk to Lin Zhanqiao.

196
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:19,540
Gu Yan.

197
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:21,140
Come in.

198
00:09:38,260 --> 00:09:39,580
We'll probably need to chat

199
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,300
for up to an hour and a half.

200
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,300
Ms. Lin, if you're busy,
you can go ahead.

201
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:45,460
Alright.

202
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,060
Have you read these contracts?

203
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:48,420
I have.

204
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:50,340
If you have, I'll just sign them.

205
00:09:51,020 --> 00:09:52,340
You should let Mr. Bei

206
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:53,500
give you a quick rundown.

207
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:55,260
If there are any clauses

208
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:56,860
you feel aren't quite right,

209
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:58,300
we can still negotiate.

210
00:09:58,620 --> 00:09:59,020
No need.

211
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:03,500
First off, you need to know

212
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:06,820
that your contract with Chenxing Culture
has been extended

213
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:08,580
from five years to eight.

214
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,380
No problem.

215
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:12,860
Second...

216
00:10:13,066 --> 00:10:14,177
I just sign here, right?

217
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:15,820
Here.

218
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,060
Yes.

219
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:47,540
(Gu Yan's blind trust in me)

220
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:48,700
(is touching,)

221
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:50,980
(but it also makes me uneasy.)

222
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:53,700
(If He Han's issue was)

223
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:55,500
(a lack of commitment,)

224
00:10:56,044 --> 00:10:58,060
(then the pressure Gu Yan
is putting on me now)

225
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,420
(is an unbearable weight.)

226
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:03,140
Ms. Lin.

227
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:06,260
Gu Yan refuses to give me his WeChat

228
00:11:06,380 --> 00:11:07,460
or any contact info.

229
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,066
I'll talk to him about it.

230
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:10,660
He's probably just shy.

231
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:12,940
No, what I mean is,
I'll do whatever it takes

232
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:14,180
to make him communicate with me.

233
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,380
I'll handle him.

234
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:17,220
Good.

235
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,380
One more thing to report.

236
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,540
Mimi started a new series.

237
00:11:24,540 --> 00:11:25,300
"Cherish Life,

238
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:26,250
Stay Away From Jerks."

239
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:26,860
Oh, you knew?

240
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:30,940
Isn't this

241
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:31,820
par for the course

242
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:32,780
for all his girlfriends?

243
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,020
When they're madly in love,

244
00:11:35,180 --> 00:11:36,577
they write "The CEO Fell For Me."

245
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:38,300
When they break up,

246
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:40,044
they write "The Jerk Chronicles."

247
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:42,300
You read it?

248
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:42,860
I...

249
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,860
I took a quick look.

250
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,380
Honestly, it's pretty vividly written.

251
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:50,355
It speaks from her heart.

252
00:11:54,140 --> 00:11:54,740
All done.

253
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:56,500
Thanks.

254
00:11:58,380 --> 00:11:59,460
Zhangzhu will walk you down.

255
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:00,100
Okay.

256
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:09,420
I'm so sorry, Mr. Bei.

257
00:12:09,820 --> 00:12:12,020
I dragged you
all the way here for nothing.

258
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:16,220
I really thought I'd have to
spend ages convincing him.

259
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:18,260
Who knew I'd be done in a few minutes?

260
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:20,020
To be honest,

261
00:12:20,860 --> 00:12:21,860
his trust in me

262
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:24,580
is both encouraging and stressful.

263
00:12:25,933 --> 00:12:27,940
That's exactly
what I wanted to warn you about.

264
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:29,220
You need to be careful.

265
00:12:39,244 --> 00:12:41,022
Has anyone ever called you two-faced?

266
00:12:46,460 --> 00:12:48,420
Authors with bad attitudes
never last long.

267
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:49,100
You know that?

268
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:50,380
Like He Han?

269
00:13:14,180 --> 00:13:15,820
When was the last time
you got to rest?

270
00:13:16,660 --> 00:13:17,700
No one is bothering you.

271
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:18,940
No meetings.

272
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:20,300
No deadlines.

273
00:13:20,460 --> 00:13:22,340
No calls, no interviews.

274
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:24,700
I bet you barely have
any WeChat messages either.

275
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,500
Pretty comfortable, right?

276
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,620
Yeah, it is.

277
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:28,940
It will stay that way for a while.

278
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:31,220
Because all the editors
are chasing Gu Yan now.

279
00:13:32,177 --> 00:13:33,500
You finally have some free time.

280
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:36,020
Why don't you take a few days off?

281
00:13:36,020 --> 00:13:37,130
Go out and have some fun.

282
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:37,700
I will.

283
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,500
But I'm worried that when I get back,

284
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,060
I'll have to hand you my resignation.

285
00:13:42,220 --> 00:13:43,260
It won't come to that.

286
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:44,644
Go on, go wherever you want.

287
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:46,260
Food, drinks, entertainment, travel,

288
00:13:46,260 --> 00:13:47,140
I'll cover it all.

289
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:49,420
For the next week,

290
00:13:49,420 --> 00:13:50,620
I'm not going anywhere.

291
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:53,540
I'm just going to stay right here
and watch you waste time.

292
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:54,860
I'm not wasting time.

293
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,500
Don't you know authors need rest?

294
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,660
We need time to reflect,

295
00:13:57,660 --> 00:13:58,980
and to experience life.

296
00:13:59,644 --> 00:14:02,177
Here are the questions
for this afternoon's interview.

297
00:14:02,420 --> 00:14:03,540
See?

298
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:05,100
Someone is bothering me now.

299
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:08,340
Take a good look
at these questions first.

300
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:10,700
They're all about Gu Yan.

301
00:14:11,820 --> 00:14:12,860
The last two aren't.

302
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:14,700
One asks if I'm still writing,

303
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,888
and the other asks
if I have a new girlfriend.

304
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:19,260
He Han.

305
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:23,500
I can cancel this interview for you.

306
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:25,220
Don't do that.

307
00:14:25,288 --> 00:14:27,822
If you do it,
then I'll have no one bothering me.

308
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:34,940
Then, don't mention
that you've met Gu Yan.

309
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:37,380
People will think
you're fixated on him.

310
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,500
Hello, Mr. He Han.

311
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,500
Have you noticed

312
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:46,180
the new author, Gu Yan,
who's exploded onto the scene recently?

313
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:47,060
Of course.

314
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:49,155
I haven't just noticed him,
and I've met him.

315
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:51,860
Don't say you've read
"Drunk Old Friend".

316
00:14:52,460 --> 00:14:53,260
Don't comment on it.

317
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:55,260
Whether you praise it or criticize it,

318
00:14:55,511 --> 00:14:56,644
it'll cause problems.

319
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:58,500
Have you read Gu Yan's novel?

320
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:00,380
I have. "Drunk Old Friend", right?

321
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,220
And what are your thoughts on it?

322
00:15:03,660 --> 00:15:04,300
It's nice.

323
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,540
But it might end badly.

324
00:15:10,133 --> 00:15:10,740
Can he really

325
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:12,177
say that in front of so many people?

326
00:15:13,020 --> 00:15:13,660
Isn't this

327
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:14,900
why he agreed to this interview?

328
00:15:14,977 --> 00:15:16,180
I don't care about that stuff.

329
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:18,222
Whatever I write,
people will read it anyway.

330
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,940
Look how smug he is.

331
00:15:25,244 --> 00:15:26,420
Will it have a bad ending?

332
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:28,700
You actually believe him?

333
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:33,020
I don't trust him on other things,

334
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:35,020
but when it comes to writing novels,

335
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:36,740
I actually trust him a bit.

336
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:39,380
He's jealous of Gu Yan.

337
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,220
He'll crash and burn first.

338
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,200
Just another half a month.

339
00:15:44,580 --> 00:15:45,511
When he starts writing

340
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:47,380
and goes head-to-head with Gu Yan,

341
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:48,860
he won't be so smug then.

342
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:54,900
A bad ending?

343
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,180
I doubt he'll even
make it to the ending.

344
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:02,288
Does it give you a thrill
to go around spreading rumors?

345
00:16:02,780 --> 00:16:04,620
Making baseless claims like that

346
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:06,740
just makes you look cheap!

347
00:16:08,755 --> 00:16:10,180
You don't care about Gu Yan, fine.

348
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:11,577
If you offend him, whatever.

349
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:12,540
But what about Dingqi?

350
00:16:12,660 --> 00:16:13,500
You're saying

351
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,740
their number-one novel is going to flop?

352
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:16,340
What?

353
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:17,460
Do you not plan

354
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:18,660
on working with Dingqi?

355
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,140
I'm telling the truth!

356
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:22,580
I'm just worried about them.

357
00:16:22,580 --> 00:16:23,540
I gave them a heads-up.

358
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:28,244
Come here.

359
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,540
I've got my phone on 0.5x speed.

360
00:16:30,540 --> 00:16:31,780
I'll play it back for you.

361
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:33,980
If you can find even a shred

362
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:35,340
of genuine concern in your voice,

363
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,580
I'll eat my phone.

364
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:38,420
No...

365
00:16:38,820 --> 00:16:40,780
I'm really doing Dingqi a favor here.

366
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,620
Think about it.

367
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:43,740
If I say
this great novel is going to flop,

368
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:45,020
won't everyone flock to read it

369
00:16:45,020 --> 00:16:46,460
just to see when it falls apart?

370
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:48,100
That's all clicks.

371
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,700
You're a good writer,

372
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:50,560
so you can be a jerk.

373
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:51,980
But you can't do nothing

374
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:53,060
and still act like a jerk!

375
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:00,460
He Han!

376
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,460
Open up. It's Mimi!

377
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:04,290
How did she get here?

378
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:05,700
How should I know?

379
00:17:06,540 --> 00:17:07,300
Why is she here?

380
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:08,740
He Han!

381
00:17:09,060 --> 00:17:11,180
I brought your favorite
Drunken Chicken Hot Pot!

382
00:17:12,260 --> 00:17:13,980
Can we just talk?

383
00:17:14,540 --> 00:17:16,020
Since when do I like Drunken Chicken?

384
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:17,460
Handle it. I'm not here.

385
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:32,900
Where's He Han?

386
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:34,500
He's not here.

387
00:17:34,980 --> 00:17:36,111
How did you get up here?

388
00:17:36,380 --> 00:17:37,300
I'm calling security.

389
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,340
I booked a room

390
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:40,300
on the 31st floor.

391
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:41,444
Right across from his.

392
00:17:42,088 --> 00:17:43,540
Calling security won't do any good.

393
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:46,180
What do you want?

394
00:17:48,020 --> 00:17:49,200
I want to apologize to him.

395
00:17:50,020 --> 00:17:51,380
He did so much for me.

396
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:53,060
And I humiliated him.

397
00:17:53,620 --> 00:17:54,980
I want to apologize in person.

398
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,977
I want us to get back together.

399
00:17:57,020 --> 00:17:58,380
No thanks, spare me.

400
00:18:01,060 --> 00:18:01,940
He has a girlfriend.

401
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:04,780
Impossible.

402
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:06,500
We broke up

403
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:07,900
less than forty-eight hours ago.

404
00:18:08,540 --> 00:18:09,060
He Han?

405
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:11,660
You think that's hard for him?

406
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:14,500
He Han!

407
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:16,780
He Han!

408
00:18:17,220 --> 00:18:17,860
He Han!

409
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:19,820
I know you're in there!

410
00:18:21,180 --> 00:18:21,860
He Han!

411
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:24,820
He Han!

412
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:29,540
He Han!

413
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:35,060
He's not here.

414
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:35,900
Just go.

415
00:18:36,980 --> 00:18:38,340
Take your drunken chicken,

416
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:41,140
and go back
to writing your "Wide Awake".

417
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,260
(Mengtong Internet Cafe)

418
00:18:53,260 --> 00:18:54,380
♪Never stop♪

419
00:18:57,577 --> 00:18:58,540
Here's your delivery.

420
00:18:58,540 --> 00:18:59,488
Leave a five-star rating.

421
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:00,260
Okay, thanks.

422
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:01,820
Er Jiu.

423
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:03,220
Food's here.

424
00:19:04,020 --> 00:19:05,060
♪Never stop♪

425
00:19:06,260 --> 00:19:07,420
Whoa, already?

426
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:09,540
I swear we just ordered.

427
00:19:10,260 --> 00:19:10,740
Hurry.

428
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,260
Give me a hand.

429
00:19:12,340 --> 00:19:13,060
Almost done.

430
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:14,300
Help me out here!

431
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,140
I'm almost done!

432
00:19:16,466 --> 00:19:17,140
It's all greasy.

433
00:19:18,177 --> 00:19:19,540
Why is it leaking so much grease?

434
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:20,220
Get some napkins.

435
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:21,020
Alright.

436
00:19:23,180 --> 00:19:24,380
No, you keep playing.

437
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:29,140
So now that you're making money writing,

438
00:19:29,311 --> 00:19:30,970
you can just
boss your girlfriend around?

439
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:34,140
You just never stop
mentioning the girlfriend.

440
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:35,580
Do you even have one?

441
00:19:36,622 --> 00:19:38,260
Why do you care if I have a girlfriend?

442
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:40,580
I'm just saying,
don't forget where you came from.

443
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:41,620
And where is that?

444
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,020
Beating you up, that's where! Log in.

445
00:19:44,180 --> 00:19:45,400
Let me finish eating first.

446
00:19:45,780 --> 00:19:46,180
Napkins.

447
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,220
♪Never stop♪

448
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:49,577
Eat this.

449
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:51,300
When you're done,
help me with the Cangwu raid.

450
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:51,780
Got it?

451
00:19:51,860 --> 00:19:53,300
Cangwu is child's play.

452
00:19:53,822 --> 00:19:56,133
I'll even carry you
through the Snowy Cave today.

453
00:19:56,688 --> 00:19:57,933
I'm taking another piece.

454
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,060
♪Never stop♪

455
00:19:59,060 --> 00:20:00,088
♪From the sea of stars♪

456
00:20:00,977 --> 00:20:01,740
Wait, seriously?

457
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:03,420
They're all gone?

458
00:20:03,711 --> 00:20:04,540
Only four pieces.

459
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:05,620
Only four?

460
00:20:05,620 --> 00:20:06,940
Why did he eat two?

461
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:08,900
Why do you eat so much?

462
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:09,940
Stop bickering.

463
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:11,220
I'll just order more.

464
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:13,540
Look at you, acting like a big shot.

465
00:20:13,940 --> 00:20:14,740
It's annoying.

466
00:20:15,888 --> 00:20:17,060
Ms. Lin is looking for me.

467
00:20:17,377 --> 00:20:18,460
I'm going to meet her.

468
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,140
Didn't you just say
we're doing the raid?

469
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:22,200
Now it's back to Ms. Lin?

470
00:20:22,580 --> 00:20:23,580
I must talk to her.

471
00:20:23,844 --> 00:20:24,620
When we're done,

472
00:20:24,980 --> 00:20:25,860
I'll help you out.

473
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:31,340
Sit down and eat.

474
00:20:34,820 --> 00:20:35,380
Forget it.

475
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,300
This was long overdue.

476
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:44,340
Congratulations on

477
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,140
your success.

478
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:46,100
Thanks.

479
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:47,820
Actually, congrats to both of us.

480
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:49,340
I brought food.

481
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,540
Is this just for me,

482
00:20:51,700 --> 00:20:52,580
or both of us?

483
00:20:52,580 --> 00:20:53,410
I haven't eaten yet.

484
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:54,288
Talk while you eat.

485
00:20:54,780 --> 00:20:55,266
Come on.

486
00:21:03,420 --> 00:21:03,700
Here.

487
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:12,300
So, tell me.

488
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:13,380
How did it feel

489
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:14,180
to go public?

490
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:16,460
I was a little nervous.

491
00:21:18,060 --> 00:21:19,020
But it wasn't so bad

492
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,177
with you there.

493
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:23,140
I just knew

494
00:21:23,911 --> 00:21:25,466
that no matter what happened,

495
00:21:26,555 --> 00:21:27,340
if I left it to you,

496
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:28,500
you'd figure it out.

497
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,820
But you need to learn
to face your readers yourself.

498
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,340
You have to learn
how to engage with them,

499
00:21:34,666 --> 00:21:35,540
answering comments,

500
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:36,800
and rallying support.

501
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:39,100
A web novelist

502
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,660
needs some social skills.

503
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,380
Many web novelists

504
00:21:42,380 --> 00:21:43,820
build their own fan circles.

505
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:45,540
It helps you connect with readers

506
00:21:45,860 --> 00:21:47,260
and show them you're genuine.

507
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:48,940
Then, they'll start promoting

508
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:50,580
your work across every platform.

509
00:21:51,155 --> 00:21:52,333
Can you do it for me?

510
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:53,340
I'm not good at that.

511
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:54,860
I can teach you.

512
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:56,660
Can you learn?

513
00:21:58,020 --> 00:21:59,140
I just want to write.

514
00:22:01,260 --> 00:22:02,777
You're a rare breed, you know that?

515
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:04,500
Most authors would die

516
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,780
to be independent fast.

517
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:06,740
That way,

518
00:22:06,740 --> 00:22:08,210
you have more leverage

519
00:22:08,210 --> 00:22:09,622
when negotiating terms later on.

520
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:11,740
I only have

521
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:13,380
one condition.

522
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:15,820
Keep writing by my side.

523
00:22:17,820 --> 00:22:18,420
No problem.

524
00:22:18,577 --> 00:22:19,666
I can promise you that.

525
00:22:21,660 --> 00:22:22,100
Who is it?

526
00:22:23,220 --> 00:22:23,620
It's me.

527
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:25,580
Coming!

528
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:30,133
Why are you here?

529
00:22:32,180 --> 00:22:33,220
I brought some fruit

530
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:34,180
for you guys.

531
00:22:34,260 --> 00:22:34,860
It's washed.

532
00:22:34,860 --> 00:22:36,100
You can snack while you talk.

533
00:22:36,380 --> 00:22:37,860
Perfect timing. Join us for a drink.

534
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:42,100
Didn't you just eat?

535
00:22:46,460 --> 00:22:47,860
Quick, pour San Mei a glass.

536
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:51,020
Better let Ms. Zhanqiao handle that.

537
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:52,460
We wanted to open a bottle,

538
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:53,100
but he refused.

539
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:54,380
I'm his boss.

540
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:55,755
He's too polite to say no to me.

541
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:57,980
I'm not big on celebrations.

542
00:22:58,180 --> 00:22:58,980
You know that.

543
00:22:59,980 --> 00:23:00,300
Here.

544
00:23:07,340 --> 00:23:08,340
Hand me a cup.

545
00:23:08,580 --> 00:23:09,860
I'll bring some up for Er Jiu.

546
00:23:17,220 --> 00:23:18,420
Enjoy your food.

547
00:23:18,540 --> 00:23:19,220
I'm heading out.

548
00:23:21,555 --> 00:23:23,088
Don't forget to help me with the raid.

549
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:24,380
I got it.

550
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:45,060
San Mei gets anxious
whenever you change even a little.

551
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:46,911
No matter how much I change,

552
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:48,755
it's not like I'm leaving this place.

553
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:50,780
Not the internet cafe.

554
00:23:50,780 --> 00:23:52,044
I'm talking about San Mei.

555
00:23:58,380 --> 00:24:00,660
(This is so exciting. I love it!)

556
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:01,580
(Gu Yan has a bright future.)
Wait, is Wang Hai

557
00:24:01,580 --> 00:24:03,180
(So young and such a good writer!)
going to have a fan base?

558
00:24:03,940 --> 00:24:04,940
No need to wait.

559
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:06,380
He's already got one.

560
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:11,020
What's wrong? Worried?

561
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:12,260
Worrying won't help.

562
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,580
There are always others.

563
00:24:14,444 --> 00:24:16,220
You can't tell whether
a fan is male or female

564
00:24:16,220 --> 00:24:17,260
from their online username.

565
00:24:17,540 --> 00:24:19,180
The fans are definitely a mix of both.

566
00:24:24,955 --> 00:24:26,020
The ones who tip a lot

567
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:27,340
must be loaded, right?

568
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:30,660
I've heard of authors hitting it big

569
00:24:30,660 --> 00:24:32,022
and ending up with their fans.

570
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:34,380
Like that guy, Ge Zhong Jian.

571
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:36,460
Ge Zhong Jian's wife

572
00:24:36,540 --> 00:24:38,180
is prettier than a movie star.

573
00:24:48,060 --> 00:24:48,780
But San Mei,

574
00:24:48,940 --> 00:24:49,540
honestly,

575
00:24:49,844 --> 00:24:52,060
if you dressed up,
you'd be prettier than any star.

576
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:54,660
No, thanks.

577
00:24:55,020 --> 00:24:56,700
I like being myself.

578
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,620
If he changes his persona every day,

579
00:24:58,620 --> 00:24:59,660
am I supposed to keep up?

580
00:24:59,860 --> 00:25:01,180
Who's going to look after my cafe?

581
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:04,420
What's the toughest part about you?

582
00:25:05,180 --> 00:25:05,580
The mouth.

583
00:25:06,660 --> 00:25:07,020
Get lost!

584
00:25:08,311 --> 00:25:08,980
Struck a nerve,

585
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:10,220
didn't I?

586
00:25:12,140 --> 00:25:13,260
What's great about this wine?

587
00:25:13,940 --> 00:25:14,660
Beer's way better.

588
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:29,060
Okay.

589
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,180
What's in the bag?

590
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:01,140
Mustard mushroom crisps.

591
00:26:01,980 --> 00:26:03,620
Flavors used to be subtle.

592
00:26:04,260 --> 00:26:05,220
Now, they are intense.

593
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:07,340
Everyone's chasing a rush.

594
00:26:08,100 --> 00:26:10,260
Without that kick,
there's no market for it.

595
00:26:15,380 --> 00:26:15,900
Want some?

596
00:26:17,060 --> 00:26:17,620
No way.

597
00:26:17,933 --> 00:26:18,660
I'm not drinking.

598
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:19,380
Absolutely not.

599
00:26:20,180 --> 00:26:21,220
I'm just testing you

600
00:26:21,220 --> 00:26:22,300
to check your resolve.

601
00:26:23,580 --> 00:26:24,380
On this street,

602
00:26:24,380 --> 00:26:26,180
no one has more resolve than me.

603
00:26:26,740 --> 00:26:27,580
I'm the most solid.

604
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:30,970
You never thought about sneaking a sip?

605
00:26:30,970 --> 00:26:32,100
No one would know.

606
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:34,060
Never.

607
00:26:35,180 --> 00:26:36,622
You'll get it when you've felt it.

608
00:26:37,460 --> 00:26:38,220
Sometimes,

609
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:39,420
your obsessions

610
00:26:39,540 --> 00:26:40,820
and the ones you'd die for

611
00:26:41,140 --> 00:26:42,260
will be gone for good

612
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:44,140
once you let go.

613
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:45,820
And other times,

614
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:47,860
the stuff you thought didn't matter

615
00:26:48,100 --> 00:26:48,900
starts haunting you

616
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:51,220
once it's actually gone.

617
00:26:54,860 --> 00:26:55,540
I hope

618
00:26:55,540 --> 00:26:57,180
I never have to
find out what it's like.

619
00:28:00,660 --> 00:28:01,740
Mr. He Han.

620
00:28:01,980 --> 00:28:02,888
Where's your boss?

621
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:04,780
She's already off.

622
00:28:10,140 --> 00:28:10,540
And you?

623
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:11,580
Still working?

624
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:14,420
I still have some work to finish.

625
00:28:15,020 --> 00:28:16,380
What work keeps you this late?

626
00:28:17,020 --> 00:28:19,170
She's making a rookie
like you work overtime.

627
00:28:19,170 --> 00:28:20,300
Lin Zhanqiao is too much.

628
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:22,380
Just head home.

629
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:23,222
Do you live far?

630
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:25,220
It's alright.

631
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:27,555
I'm not offering you a ride.

632
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:29,540
I'm just saying, if you live far,

633
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:30,700
be careful taking a cab.

634
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:32,180
Use the phone's safety feature.

635
00:28:32,288 --> 00:28:34,088
Set Lin Zhanqiao
as your emergency contact.

636
00:28:34,090 --> 00:28:36,000
She's making you stay late,
so she's responsible.

637
00:28:36,580 --> 00:28:37,700
She didn't make me stay.

638
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:38,620
I chose to work late.

639
00:28:38,620 --> 00:28:39,580
Don't defend her.

640
00:28:39,580 --> 00:28:40,500
If a boss is unfair,

641
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:41,580
you can push back.

642
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:43,180
Who actually wants to work late?

643
00:28:43,380 --> 00:28:44,700
Wouldn't you rather sleep or read?

644
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:45,340
No, really.

645
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:47,300
I'm honestly
just the type who works late.

646
00:28:49,020 --> 00:28:50,810
Ambition is great, girl,

647
00:28:50,810 --> 00:28:52,022
but this isn't the smart way.

648
00:28:52,220 --> 00:28:53,820
It's not about ambition.

649
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:55,180
What's it about?

650
00:28:56,820 --> 00:28:58,380
I just don't want to go home.

651
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:00,980
Trouble at home?

652
00:29:01,820 --> 00:29:02,511
More or less.

653
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,866
Good luck with that.

654
00:29:12,980 --> 00:29:14,140
Hey, don't come back yet.

655
00:29:15,380 --> 00:29:17,300
Mimi got a room
right across from yours.

656
00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:19,100
She's sitting
outside your door waiting.

657
00:29:39,740 --> 00:29:40,580
I'm suddenly free.

658
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,900
If you feel like talking
about your home situation,

659
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:44,300
I can stick around for a bit.

660
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:57,100
My dad is getting remarried.

661
00:29:58,860 --> 00:30:00,740
He's moving
my stepmother in to live with me.

662
00:30:01,220 --> 00:30:01,820
I hate it.

663
00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:03,340
Hate that he's remarrying,

664
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:05,822
or just that you have to live with her?

665
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:08,620
Both.

666
00:30:09,300 --> 00:30:10,260
When my dad

667
00:30:10,355 --> 00:30:12,020
picks a wife,
he only cares about looks,

668
00:30:12,020 --> 00:30:12,860
not about substance.

669
00:30:15,700 --> 00:30:16,460
I can tell.

670
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:18,740
How can you tell?

671
00:30:18,820 --> 00:30:19,380
Your mom

672
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:20,940
must have been quite a beauty.

673
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:32,140
My mom passed away.

674
00:30:35,020 --> 00:30:35,580
I'm so sorry.

675
00:30:37,180 --> 00:30:37,660
It's okay.

676
00:30:38,220 --> 00:30:39,740
She really was beautiful.

677
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:41,060
But she was a natural beauty.

678
00:30:41,222 --> 00:30:42,620
I'm not sure about this new woman.

679
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:46,220
Stop calling her "stepmother."

680
00:30:46,500 --> 00:30:47,860
It's 2024.

681
00:30:47,940 --> 00:30:49,740
This isn't Snow White or Cinderella.

682
00:30:49,933 --> 00:30:51,688
Your dad's new wife
is just his new wife.

683
00:30:51,733 --> 00:30:52,960
She has nothing to do with you.

684
00:30:52,980 --> 00:30:54,420
Stepmom, second mom, or whatever...

685
00:30:54,580 --> 00:30:56,100
Your own mother is irreplaceable.

686
00:30:56,180 --> 00:30:56,700
Right?

687
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:58,660
You can't stop him
from getting married,

688
00:30:58,820 --> 00:30:59,820
but that's his business.

689
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:01,660
You can certainly set boundaries.

690
00:31:02,180 --> 00:31:03,380
So, you're on my side?

691
00:31:03,540 --> 00:31:04,780
Let me finish.

692
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:06,620
Look.

693
00:31:08,420 --> 00:31:09,660
Who bought your house?

694
00:31:11,820 --> 00:31:12,300
My dad.

695
00:31:13,020 --> 00:31:13,900
He's a contractor.

696
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:14,660
He builds houses.

697
00:31:14,660 --> 00:31:15,180
He's loaded.

698
00:31:15,180 --> 00:31:15,620
Exactly.

699
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:17,100
The house belongs to him.

700
00:31:17,300 --> 00:31:18,660
He's the master of that home.

701
00:31:18,860 --> 00:31:20,420
He has the right to let someone move in.

702
00:31:20,540 --> 00:31:21,688
But you have a choice, too.

703
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:22,900
You're an adult now.

704
00:31:23,180 --> 00:31:24,580
You can choose to leave.

705
00:31:28,100 --> 00:31:29,610
I have no money, no house.

706
00:31:29,610 --> 00:31:30,300
Then you know

707
00:31:30,300 --> 00:31:31,940
what your goal is from here on out.

708
00:31:31,940 --> 00:31:32,820
Make some money.

709
00:31:32,900 --> 00:31:34,140
Rent a place and move out.

710
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:35,420
Until then, you'll live under

711
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:36,460
someone else's roof.

712
00:31:36,460 --> 00:31:37,060
No choice.

713
00:31:37,311 --> 00:31:38,460
Everyone goes through it.

714
00:31:38,460 --> 00:31:39,620
We spend years fighting

715
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:40,980
just to gain that independence.

716
00:31:41,140 --> 00:31:42,580
But remember one thing.

717
00:31:43,460 --> 00:31:44,820
Do it on your own terms.

718
00:31:44,940 --> 00:31:46,066
Don't rely on anyone.

719
00:31:46,540 --> 00:31:47,420
You're pretty enough

720
00:31:47,420 --> 00:31:48,844
that you could marry into a house.

721
00:31:49,020 --> 00:31:50,140
Don't laugh. I'm serious.

722
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:52,860
But then it's someone else's house,

723
00:31:53,740 --> 00:31:54,610
not yours.

724
00:31:54,610 --> 00:31:56,220
If they ever want you out,

725
00:31:56,220 --> 00:31:56,780
what then?

726
00:31:57,220 --> 00:31:57,980
Squat there?

727
00:31:58,180 --> 00:31:59,020
Sue them?

728
00:31:59,540 --> 00:32:00,220
It gets ugly.

729
00:32:04,540 --> 00:32:05,820
I'll talk with my dad.

730
00:32:05,955 --> 00:32:07,220
Don't tell him it was my idea.

731
00:32:07,980 --> 00:32:08,500
Why not?

732
00:32:09,244 --> 00:32:10,500
Tell him it came from your boss.

733
00:32:12,666 --> 00:32:13,420
Aren't you leaving?

734
00:32:13,500 --> 00:32:14,740
I'll stay a bit longer. Go home.

735
00:32:15,140 --> 00:32:16,020
I'll lock the door.

736
00:32:20,300 --> 00:32:22,250
Don't worry.
There are cameras everywhere.

737
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:23,050
I'm a public figure.

738
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:24,380
I have an image to maintain.

739
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:48,380
Ready?

740
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:50,340
We're about to tackle

741
00:32:50,340 --> 00:32:51,844
the hardest part of the story so far.

742
00:32:54,820 --> 00:32:56,060
The route we took previously

743
00:32:56,580 --> 00:32:57,580
bypassed Guazhou and

744
00:32:58,140 --> 00:32:59,300
went straight to Zhichi Gorge,

745
00:32:59,580 --> 00:33:00,580
reaching Zhegutian.

746
00:33:02,940 --> 00:33:04,740
Guazhou was mentioned constantly,

747
00:33:05,140 --> 00:33:06,900
yet the story just skipped over it.

748
00:33:07,380 --> 00:33:08,620
That never made sense to me.

749
00:33:10,220 --> 00:33:11,660
You and He Han mapped out

750
00:33:11,660 --> 00:33:13,088
the outline and the route together.

751
00:33:13,340 --> 00:33:13,860
Why did you

752
00:33:14,140 --> 00:33:15,500
bypass Guazhou back then?

753
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:20,300
Because the plot was stolen.

754
00:33:29,260 --> 00:33:32,220
(2019)

755
00:33:43,540 --> 00:33:44,100
What's wrong?

756
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:45,020
Read it.

757
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:46,260
What is this?

758
00:33:52,980 --> 00:33:53,260
Wait...

759
00:33:54,340 --> 00:33:55,140
Who wrote this?

760
00:33:55,140 --> 00:33:56,780
Looks familiar, doesn't it?

761
00:33:57,460 --> 00:33:57,940
Exactly.

762
00:33:57,940 --> 00:33:59,300
That's your Guazhou storyline.

763
00:33:59,555 --> 00:34:01,700
Someone rebranded it
and passed it off as their own!

764
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:02,820
You're still on the outline,

765
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:04,420
but they've published the full text.

766
00:34:04,700 --> 00:34:05,980
Who wrote this?

767
00:34:05,980 --> 00:34:07,340
How should I know?

768
00:34:07,500 --> 00:34:08,460
I was going to ask you.

769
00:34:09,340 --> 00:34:10,730
Who did you tell about this?

770
00:34:10,730 --> 00:34:11,620
No one.

771
00:34:11,820 --> 00:34:12,540
That's impossible.

772
00:34:16,020 --> 00:34:17,500
How did it leak?

773
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:23,180
Someone must have

774
00:34:23,866 --> 00:34:25,511
snapped a photo of the draft.

775
00:34:26,740 --> 00:34:27,820
So we decided

776
00:34:28,580 --> 00:34:29,980
to design a completely new route.

777
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:36,340
(Zhichi Gorge)

778
00:34:50,860 --> 00:34:52,700
Let's hold off on writing
until I've figured out

779
00:34:53,340 --> 00:34:54,020
how to rewrite

780
00:34:54,260 --> 00:34:54,980
the Guazhou arc.

781
00:34:59,260 --> 00:35:00,980
In a million-word novel,

782
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:04,980
not every single chapter
has to be perfect

783
00:35:05,900 --> 00:35:07,420
before it reaches the readers.

784
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:13,300
I disagree.

785
00:35:19,060 --> 00:35:20,780
So we moved on to the Zhichi Gorge.

786
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:22,580
We followed that plan,

787
00:35:22,980 --> 00:35:24,220
only to realize afterward

788
00:35:24,860 --> 00:35:27,266
it wasn't nearly as good
as the original Guazhou arc.

789
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:30,260
Is that why

790
00:35:30,740 --> 00:35:31,460
Drunk Old Friend

791
00:35:31,460 --> 00:35:32,380
was never finished?

792
00:35:33,420 --> 00:35:33,740
Yes.

793
00:35:34,580 --> 00:35:35,700
He insisted on finding a way

794
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:37,660
to top the original Guazhou arc

795
00:35:37,777 --> 00:35:38,955
before he'd start writing.

796
00:35:39,540 --> 00:35:40,340
But he never did?

797
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:41,100
Never.

798
00:35:43,740 --> 00:35:44,260
Let's do it.

799
00:35:44,733 --> 00:35:45,700
Take the Guazhou route.

800
00:35:46,380 --> 00:35:48,020
He Han couldn't do it, but maybe we can.

801
00:35:49,700 --> 00:35:51,060
But you don't have much time.

802
00:35:51,580 --> 00:35:52,780
You have three days at most.

803
00:35:53,180 --> 00:35:54,260
If you haven't

804
00:35:54,380 --> 00:35:55,700
figured it out by then,

805
00:35:56,220 --> 00:35:57,180
you'll miss the update.

806
00:35:57,540 --> 00:35:58,340
I want to try.

807
00:35:59,060 --> 00:36:00,660
I want to prove I'm better than He Han.

808
00:36:05,780 --> 00:36:07,100
Is the lore book still around?

809
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,511
I'll ask He Han for it.

810
00:36:14,111 --> 00:36:15,020
You have to trust me.

811
00:36:15,460 --> 00:36:17,140
I might not be as gifted as he is,

812
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:19,740
but I'm more hardworking

813
00:36:20,180 --> 00:36:21,020
and younger.

814
00:36:21,700 --> 00:36:22,660
Most importantly,

815
00:36:22,740 --> 00:36:24,422
I'll be a better partner than he was.

816
00:36:25,340 --> 00:36:25,740
Of course.

817
00:36:26,500 --> 00:36:28,500
I might not surpass the Phantom Knight,

818
00:36:28,780 --> 00:36:30,060
but I'll surpass He Han.

819
00:36:30,660 --> 00:36:31,460
Once I do,

820
00:36:31,700 --> 00:36:32,700
you'll have done it too.

821
00:36:33,620 --> 00:36:35,300
I don't want to hear anyone saying

822
00:36:35,820 --> 00:36:37,333
you're just riding He Han's coattails

823
00:36:37,420 --> 00:36:38,466
or living in his shadow.

824
00:36:39,940 --> 00:36:40,500
Thank you.

825
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:42,260
But it all starts

826
00:36:42,860 --> 00:36:44,780
with writing those pages every day.

827
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:54,580
(On Love: Thirty Thousand Chapters,
By the Phantom Knight)

828
00:36:56,900 --> 00:36:57,380
Ms. Lin.

829
00:36:59,500 --> 00:37:00,620
Don't hand me off to anyone.

830
00:37:01,940 --> 00:37:02,940
Zhangzhu is my assistant.

831
00:37:03,155 --> 00:37:05,044
She only handles
the administrative stuff.

832
00:37:05,340 --> 00:37:06,420
I only want to deal with you.

833
00:37:07,340 --> 00:37:07,860
I understand.

834
00:37:08,540 --> 00:37:08,940
Okay.

835
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:17,220
I'll walk you to your car.

836
00:37:17,380 --> 00:37:18,377
It's fine. Go back inside.

837
00:37:18,420 --> 00:37:19,100
I can manage.

838
00:37:19,220 --> 00:37:19,822
Are you sure?

839
00:37:19,940 --> 00:37:20,380
Yeah.

840
00:37:20,740 --> 00:37:21,020
Bye.

841
00:37:21,420 --> 00:37:21,740
Bye.

842
00:37:21,940 --> 00:37:22,260
Alright.

843
00:37:22,460 --> 00:37:23,133
Get home safe.

844
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:23,580
Okay.

845
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:28,822
We've been waiting. Come on.

846
00:37:29,460 --> 00:37:30,380
I'm here, my lady.

847
00:37:39,822 --> 00:37:41,460
So you invited someone over for drinks

848
00:37:41,860 --> 00:37:43,580
and let them snap photos
of the lore book?

849
00:37:44,620 --> 00:37:45,940
No way.

850
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:46,940
Really?

851
00:37:48,180 --> 00:37:49,420
I don't remember. I'm not sure.

852
00:37:49,420 --> 00:37:50,420
What do you mean?

853
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:52,300
That editor was a pretty girl,

854
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:54,660
and she came here,
and you two had a drink.

855
00:37:54,660 --> 00:37:55,540
That's a fact, right?

856
00:37:55,740 --> 00:37:57,100
Yes, she was here.

857
00:37:57,340 --> 00:37:59,060
But only she drank.
I didn't touch a drop.

858
00:37:59,180 --> 00:38:00,860
Besides, you said you were done with me

859
00:38:00,860 --> 00:38:02,380
and told me to find a better editor.

860
00:38:02,540 --> 00:38:04,180
I told you to find an editor,

861
00:38:04,180 --> 00:38:05,580
not a girl.

862
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:06,940
I wasn't looking for a girl.

863
00:38:06,940 --> 00:38:08,540
The editor just happened to be female.

864
00:38:08,688 --> 00:38:09,540
Aren't you one, too?

865
00:38:09,540 --> 00:38:10,260
So what?

866
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:12,060
Fine. It's your choice to indulge

867
00:38:12,060 --> 00:38:12,820
in pleasure.

868
00:38:12,820 --> 00:38:13,340
But you can't

869
00:38:13,340 --> 00:38:15,010
let it cause a major mistake at work!

870
00:38:15,010 --> 00:38:16,940
I already told you, I wasn't drinking.

871
00:38:16,940 --> 00:38:17,540
And I wasn't

872
00:38:17,540 --> 00:38:19,180
doing any bad stuff you're imagining.

873
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:20,780
Of course you wouldn't admit it.

874
00:38:20,780 --> 00:38:22,180
Because I didn't do it!

875
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:23,100
How did they

876
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:23,900
snap those photos?

877
00:38:24,140 --> 00:38:25,660
I don't remember, okay? I don't know.

878
00:38:25,660 --> 00:38:26,460
"I don't remember anything."

879
00:38:26,460 --> 00:38:27,911
Is that the best excuse you've got?

880
00:38:28,100 --> 00:38:29,060
Look, maybe she took them

881
00:38:29,060 --> 00:38:30,420
while I was in the bathroom.

882
00:38:30,660 --> 00:38:31,540
Right? I don't know.

883
00:38:32,380 --> 00:38:33,500
Can you stop being angry?

884
00:38:33,580 --> 00:38:34,400
Fine, I admit it.

885
00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:35,420
It's on me.

886
00:38:35,420 --> 00:38:36,860
It's my fault. I'll fix it.

887
00:38:37,420 --> 00:38:38,820
But don't just label me as some guy

888
00:38:38,820 --> 00:38:39,700
who ruins everything

889
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:40,930
over booze and women.

890
00:38:40,930 --> 00:38:42,177
Is that who you think I am?

891
00:38:48,220 --> 00:38:48,500
Me...

892
00:38:49,300 --> 00:38:50,866
Haven't you messed up enough already?

893
00:39:45,580 --> 00:39:46,340
Have some water.

894
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:50,311
You're still here?

895
00:39:52,820 --> 00:39:54,180
Stay and talk to me for a bit.

896
00:39:55,740 --> 00:39:56,020
Okay.

897
00:39:57,820 --> 00:39:59,100
Forget the water.

898
00:39:59,100 --> 00:39:59,820
Try this instead.

899
00:40:10,940 --> 00:40:11,620
Mr. He Han...

900
00:40:12,260 --> 00:40:13,660
I've really wanted to write, too.

901
00:40:14,380 --> 00:40:15,460
Do I have what it takes?

902
00:40:15,700 --> 00:40:16,820
Sure. Why not?

903
00:40:16,900 --> 00:40:18,020
Writing is simple.

904
00:40:18,780 --> 00:40:21,260
Did Ms. Lin ever write?

905
00:40:21,700 --> 00:40:22,300
She did,

906
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:23,820
just not as good as I am.

907
00:40:24,140 --> 00:40:24,980
So, she quit.

908
00:40:25,355 --> 00:40:26,340
If you put it that way,

909
00:40:26,340 --> 00:40:27,980
no one's better than you.

910
00:40:27,980 --> 00:40:28,940
Everyone should give up.

911
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:30,980
Others don't care, but she does.

912
00:40:31,180 --> 00:40:32,420
Hence, she can't write.

913
00:40:34,740 --> 00:40:35,900
What genre are you into?

914
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:39,620
I want to write something

915
00:40:39,620 --> 00:40:40,820
that you can't.

916
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:42,740
Something I can't?

917
00:40:43,020 --> 00:40:44,460
I'm all ears.

918
00:40:45,460 --> 00:40:46,300
Stuff like Mimi's.

919
00:40:47,700 --> 00:40:49,100
Yeah, I can't write that.

920
00:40:55,044 --> 00:40:55,620
Heading out?

921
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:56,460
Morning.

922
00:41:33,220 --> 00:41:34,260
I'm going to bed.

923
00:41:39,620 --> 00:41:40,420
Morning, Zhao.

924
00:41:40,500 --> 00:41:40,860
Morning.

925
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:43,660
Where's Wang Hai?

926
00:41:44,780 --> 00:41:45,500
He went to sleep.

927
00:41:45,860 --> 00:41:46,260
Breakfast.

928
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:26,860
I bought you breakfast.

929
00:42:26,860 --> 00:42:27,780
Get up and eat.

930
00:42:28,500 --> 00:42:29,860
You didn't eat all night.

931
00:43:04,977 --> 00:43:05,777
How old are you?

932
00:43:05,955 --> 00:43:07,380
You don't seem that young anymore.

933
00:43:07,540 --> 00:43:09,466
You need to apologize
for the toxic ideas

934
00:43:09,511 --> 00:43:11,100
you've been feeding my daughter.

935
00:43:11,911 --> 00:43:13,060
What did you say to Zhangzhu?

936
00:43:13,177 --> 00:43:14,422
Her father just came to the office

937
00:43:14,444 --> 00:43:16,266
specifically to give me
a piece of his mind.

938
00:43:18,140 --> 00:43:19,180
It's expensive.

939
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:20,940
Don't be fooled by how

940
00:43:20,940 --> 00:43:22,540
I like chatting with those young girls.

941
00:43:22,820 --> 00:43:23,580
It's meaningless.

942
00:43:25,688 --> 00:43:27,380
It's one thing for you
to take advantage of me,

943
00:43:27,380 --> 00:43:28,820
but why should I let

944
00:43:29,060 --> 00:43:29,940
other men do it?

945
00:43:30,580 --> 00:43:32,500
Does Lawyer Bei
know what you're really like

946
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:33,500
in front of your mother?

947
00:43:33,780 --> 00:43:34,260
He doesn't.

948
00:43:35,361 --> 00:43:36,481
(I've been thinking.)

949
00:43:37,761 --> 00:43:41,041
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

950
00:43:41,801 --> 00:43:49,131
(is probably different.)

951
00:43:50,131 --> 00:43:51,881
♪If the sky♪

952
00:43:52,391 --> 00:43:53,791
♪And the sea♪

953
00:43:54,331 --> 00:43:56,041
♪Turned upside down♪

954
00:43:57,601 --> 00:43:59,531
♪If a swimming fish♪

955
00:43:59,931 --> 00:44:03,321
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

956
00:44:05,091 --> 00:44:07,061
♪If back then♪

957
00:44:07,421 --> 00:44:11,831
♪We had never let go♪

958
00:44:12,431 --> 00:44:18,711
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

959
00:44:19,831 --> 00:44:21,981
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

960
00:44:21,981 --> 00:44:23,851
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

961
00:44:24,031 --> 00:44:26,471
♪And found our way back whole♪

962
00:44:27,311 --> 00:44:29,481
♪So let this surging love♪

963
00:44:29,481 --> 00:44:33,911
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

964
00:44:34,811 --> 00:44:36,991
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

965
00:44:36,991 --> 00:44:38,081
♪That's alright♪

966
00:44:38,621 --> 00:44:39,371
♪If we're buried♪

967
00:44:39,371 --> 00:44:42,071
♪By passing years all the better♪

968
00:44:42,331 --> 00:44:44,511
♪At least we still can keep♪

969
00:44:44,691 --> 00:44:49,111
♪This one eternal photograph♪

970
00:45:04,871 --> 00:45:07,161
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

971
00:45:07,161 --> 00:45:08,921
♪Running in opposite ways♪

972
00:45:09,041 --> 00:45:11,511
♪Searching all along the way♪

973
00:45:12,311 --> 00:45:14,471
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

974
00:45:14,661 --> 00:45:19,571
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

975
00:45:19,571 --> 00:45:23,091
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

976
00:45:23,331 --> 00:45:24,301
♪Only after loss♪

977
00:45:24,301 --> 00:45:26,931
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

978
00:45:27,341 --> 00:45:29,701
♪In another time and space♪

979
00:45:29,701 --> 00:45:31,261
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

980
00:45:31,261 --> 00:45:34,091
♪Till we grow old♪

981
00:45:35,051 --> 00:45:37,341
♪But still the sky will never♪

982
00:45:37,341 --> 00:45:40,011
♪Turn with the sea♪

983
00:45:42,531 --> 00:45:44,941
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

984
00:45:44,941 --> 00:45:50,151
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
